🧠 Interview Narration Tip
“In real projects, Docker errors usually fall into categories: build errors due to bad Dockerfiles, runtime issues like port conflicts or resource limits, networking misconfigurations, and container crashes. The key is to check logs, validate Dockerfile syntax, and isolate the failing component. I always emphasize using docker logs, docker inspect, and resource monitoring to troubleshoot quickly.”